Project example using the FastAPI framework with asynchronous access to the Postgres database.

Within the project, execute:

docker-compose up

This command starts the postgre database container.

The ideal is to create a virtual environment (pipenv), and then execute the commands below:

pip install fastapi
pip install uvicorn
pip install sqlalchemy
pip install databases
pip install passlib
pip install psycopg2
pip install pydantic
pip install python-jose
pip install pyjwt
pip install asyncpg

After creating the virtual environment and installing the dependencies, start the server with the command below:

uvicorn app.src.main:app --reload

Open the browser in the url below to access OpenAPI (old swagger)...

http://127.0.0.1:8000/docs#
